1
00:01:27,390 --> 00:01:31,890
[The Dark Romance]

2
00:01:32,160 --> 00:01:34,940
[Episode 15]

3
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:38,229
[Xinsheng International Law Firm]

4
00:01:38,590 --> 00:01:41,000
Ding Zhibo and Oceanvision International
had a lawyer's letter sent to you,

5
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:43,070
purely out
of public relations considerations—

6
00:01:43,070 --> 00:01:45,590
they're trying to deny
the allegations completely.

7
00:01:45,590 --> 00:01:46,640
But I don't believe

8
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:48,280
they'll actually sue.

9
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:50,789
You didn't film or share

10
00:01:50,789 --> 00:01:51,990
those videos online,

11
00:01:52,350 --> 00:01:52,840
so your actions do not constitute

12
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:55,350
the required elements
for a defamation lawsuit.

13
00:01:55,350 --> 00:01:58,080
The court most likely
won't even accept the case.

14
00:01:58,950 --> 00:02:00,010
Thank you, Senior.

15
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:01,760
The things

16
00:02:02,350 --> 00:02:03,550
you said in the video,

17
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:04,920
are they all true?

18
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,960
In that case, their public lawyer's letter
on social media

19
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:15,680
actually constitutes

20
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:17,410
defamation against you.

21
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:18,680
If you'd like,

22
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:19,740
I can represent you

23
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:21,130
and file a countersuit.

24
00:02:23,910 --> 00:02:25,410
But if we countersue,

25
00:02:25,710 --> 00:02:27,910
they probably won't just let it go, right?

26
00:02:27,910 --> 00:02:30,470
Ding Zhibo is now categorically
denying everything.

27
00:02:30,470 --> 00:02:32,400
But once we fight back

28
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:33,520
and he realizes

29
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:35,430
he can't just walk away,

30
00:02:36,190 --> 00:02:37,720
his next move will likely be

31
00:02:38,280 --> 00:02:39,750
smearing you

32
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:41,860
and vilifying the victim.

33
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,360
It's their standard playbook:

34
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:46,120
we've seen many such cases.

35
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:47,920
Smearing her?

36
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:49,240
Basically,

37
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:51,910
they'll attack Yan Ling's character

38
00:02:51,910 --> 00:02:54,560
and spread fabricated "facts"

39
00:02:54,870 --> 00:02:56,840
to undermine public trust in you.

40
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:58,360
That's exactly the kind of dramatic twist

41
00:02:58,360 --> 00:02:59,690
the online crowd loves.

42
00:03:00,870 --> 00:03:01,930
If it comes to that,

43
00:03:02,310 --> 00:03:04,560
it would only retraumatize the victim.

44
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:09,710
I can't be

45
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:11,740
Ding Zhibo's only victim.

46
00:03:13,290 --> 00:03:15,520
Isn't there any way the law
can hold him accountable?

47
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:17,000
I've heard that the police

48
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,190
have already started

49
00:03:18,190 --> 00:03:20,000
investigating their charity foundation,

50
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,560
but someone like Ding Zhibo,
who's been around for a long time,

51
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:23,220
is definitely very cautious.

52
00:03:23,590 --> 00:03:24,720
Just like this time,

53
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:27,150
he most likely took the children abroad,

54
00:03:27,150 --> 00:03:28,840
which has made the investigation
even harder.

55
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:29,970
Moreover, he's very good

56
00:03:29,970 --> 00:03:31,770
at covering up his crimes,

57
00:03:32,150 --> 00:03:33,880
and the victims' sense of shame

58
00:03:34,030 --> 00:03:35,150
will be even stronger.

59
00:03:35,150 --> 00:03:36,640
Not everyone has your courage

60
00:03:36,640 --> 00:03:38,470
to speak out and identify him.

61
00:03:44,910 --> 00:03:46,400
It's not about courage.

62
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:50,560
To be honest,

63
00:03:51,030 --> 00:03:51,560
Yan Ling,

64
00:03:54,310 --> 00:03:55,710
I used to look down on you.

65
00:03:57,710 --> 00:03:59,030
Back in school,

66
00:03:59,750 --> 00:04:01,150
when I saw him pick you up,

67
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:03,800
I naively assumed

68
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:07,000
you were the kind of girl

69
00:04:07,590 --> 00:04:08,920
people gossiped about.

70
00:04:10,470 --> 00:04:11,430
Until now,

71
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:13,450
after these recent interactions,

72
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:15,630
especially throughout this incident
with Ding Zhibo,

73
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:16,760
I've come to realize

74
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:18,120
I was wrong

75
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:20,250
to believe such a one-sided illusion.

76
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:21,959
I'm sorry—

77
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:24,750
for my arrogance back then,

78
00:04:25,430 --> 00:04:27,160
and for my mean-spiritedness.

79
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:30,360
You don't have to decide

80
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:31,760
right now whether to sue.

81
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:33,120
Whenever you're ready,

82
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,120
just say the word.

83
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:40,700
No matter what you decide,

84
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:42,100
I've got your back.

85
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:45,120
You two...

86
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,200
Is that what I think it is?

87
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:51,560
Senior,

88
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:54,700
these are our wedding sweets.

89
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:56,070
I

90
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:58,240
knew something was up

91
00:04:58,240 --> 00:04:59,040
the first time

92
00:05:00,510 --> 00:05:01,770
I saw you two together.

93
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,860
Alright, we're home.

94
00:05:19,510 --> 00:05:20,160
Honey,

95
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:21,870
I'm starving.

96
00:05:22,510 --> 00:05:25,120
What do you think Mom will
have cooked for us tonight?

97
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:26,480
I bet she will have made braised pork.

98
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:27,270
Really?

99
00:05:27,270 --> 00:05:31,070
-I casually acted cute this morning...
-You asked for it this morning.

100
00:05:31,070 --> 00:05:34,720
-and she took it seriously.
-I think she likes you more than me now.

101
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:35,480
Okay.

102
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:41,720
It's the hospital's call.

103
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:42,650
Let me answer it.

104
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:44,180
I'll head upstairs and wait for you.

105
00:05:44,180 --> 00:05:44,750
Sounds good.

106
00:05:44,750 --> 00:05:45,430
Hurry up.

107
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:52,300
Why are you calling me?

108
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:53,290
We're busted.

109
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:55,010
She spotted me just now.

110
00:05:55,070 --> 00:05:55,670
Who was it?

111
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:57,440
Your mother-in-law.

112
00:05:57,630 --> 00:05:58,600
It just happened,

113
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:00,530
at my supermarket on Dongtai Road.

114
00:06:03,520 --> 00:06:05,250
I told you to lay low for a while.

115
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:07,300
What did she say to you?

116
00:06:07,900 --> 00:06:09,480
She asked when I got back.

117
00:06:12,070 --> 00:06:13,270
What did you tell her?

118
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:16,720
I just said,

119
00:06:17,070 --> 00:06:18,800
"You've got the wrong person."

120
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:19,630
Got it.

121
00:06:56,920 --> 00:06:57,630
Yan Ling...

122
00:06:57,909 --> 00:06:58,350
Mom,

123
00:06:59,950 --> 00:07:01,000
what are you up to?

124
00:07:02,420 --> 00:07:03,920
What were you two talking about?

125
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:05,120
N-Nothing much.

126
00:07:05,430 --> 00:07:07,690
I was just looking for a pair of scissors.

127
00:07:08,950 --> 00:07:10,880
Do you know where the scissors are?

128
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:13,240
Mom wants to make a photo wall for Jiale.

129
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:16,360
There's a pair in the study.

130
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:17,420
I'll get it for you.

131
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:18,240
Sure.

132
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:19,310
Go get changed first.

133
00:07:19,310 --> 00:07:19,750
Okay.

134
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:34,070
Mom.

135
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:45,780
Look how adorable Jiale was
in these childhood photos.

136
00:07:47,070 --> 00:07:48,810
I've been here for a couple of days now—

137
00:07:48,810 --> 00:07:49,680
how come you haven't

138
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:50,720
called your mom?

139
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:54,060
I called her a few days ago.

140
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:56,510
She mentioned my aunt
isn't recovering well after surgery,

141
00:07:56,510 --> 00:07:59,640
so she's been staying
at the hospital to take care of her.

142
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:02,800
Mom,

143
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:06,490
did you need something from my mother?

144
00:08:08,110 --> 00:08:09,560
No, nothing in particular.

145
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:11,020
I've been thinking of her.

146
00:08:14,510 --> 00:08:15,000
Mom,

147
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,200
the lawyer said today

148
00:08:17,750 --> 00:08:20,120
that the court won't accept
Ding Zhibo's lawsuit.

149
00:08:20,120 --> 00:08:21,920
You don't need to worry anymore.

150
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:24,720
What?

151
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:26,760
You already told Mom?

152
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:28,000
Not yet.

153
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:29,800
Mom was just asking

154
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:32,600
how my aunt's recovery
is going after the surgery.

155
00:08:37,750 --> 00:08:38,750
Wow, something

156
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:40,409
smells amazing.

157
00:08:41,909 --> 00:08:42,270
Mom,

158
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:44,970
did you really make red-braised pork?

159
00:08:45,150 --> 00:08:46,550
You're way too good to me.

160
00:08:50,630 --> 00:08:51,270
Let's eat.

161
00:08:51,750 --> 00:08:52,200
Okay.

162
00:08:52,910 --> 00:08:53,510
Come on,

163
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:54,520
I'm starving.

164
00:08:55,360 --> 00:08:56,020
Hurry over.

165
00:08:59,150 --> 00:09:00,550
There are so many dishes.

166
00:09:09,910 --> 00:09:11,170
Mom, you don't have to do all this—

167
00:09:11,170 --> 00:09:11,870
let me help.

168
00:09:12,830 --> 00:09:13,520
It's fine.

169
00:09:13,670 --> 00:09:15,130
Yan Ling can give me a hand.

170
00:09:15,420 --> 00:09:16,550
You're letting her help?

171
00:09:16,550 --> 00:09:17,210
Better not.

172
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:19,170
Have you seen her nails?

173
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:21,910
She's getting her wedding photos
taken tomorrow—

174
00:09:21,910 --> 00:09:23,840
she even got a manicure
for the first time ever.

175
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:24,670
Do they look nice?

176
00:09:24,670 --> 00:09:27,330
Well, don't let her ruin them
by washing dishes.

177
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:28,480
Honey,

178
00:09:28,750 --> 00:09:30,360
I think you should hurry up
and take a shower,

179
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:30,960
then put on a face mask,

180
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:32,960
so you'll look beautiful tomorrow.

181
00:09:35,550 --> 00:09:36,910
Then you help out more, okay?

182
00:09:36,910 --> 00:09:38,320
Don't let Mom overwork herself.

183
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:38,850
Alright.

184
00:09:40,150 --> 00:09:42,210
Mom, I'm off to go pamper myself a bit.

185
00:10:02,040 --> 00:10:03,480
Typhoon No. 5 of the year

186
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:05,440
is expected to make landfall
in our city tonight.

187
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:07,550
China's National Meteorological Center
has issued a red warning.

188
00:10:07,550 --> 00:10:09,320
Heavy rain will continue
through tomorrow morning—

189
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:12,250
residents are advised
to avoid unnecessary travel.

190
00:10:18,670 --> 00:10:19,720
But you know,

191
00:10:19,750 --> 00:10:22,360
I feel like my acting has
become much more relaxed lately.

192
00:10:22,360 --> 00:10:23,510
I'm not as nervous as I used to be.

193
00:10:23,510 --> 00:10:24,220
Oh really?

194
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:25,380
We have a customer.

195
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:29,840
Mrs. Luo,

196
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:31,630
you're back.

197
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:38,630
Mom.

198
00:10:40,620 --> 00:10:42,020
You're all here already!

199
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:43,660
Welcome, welcome.

200
00:10:43,670 --> 00:10:44,240
Hello.

201
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:44,550
Hello,

202
00:10:44,550 --> 00:10:45,680
Ms. Su.

203
00:11:22,490 --> 00:11:26,210
[General Higher Education
Graduation Certificate]

204
00:11:29,040 --> 00:11:32,060
[Name: Luo Liang]
[Collage: Tianfu Medical University]

205
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:35,510
Mom,

206
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:37,480
what are you looking for?

207
00:11:37,480 --> 00:11:38,550
Nothing, really.

208
00:11:39,390 --> 00:11:41,910
Just haven't finished
organizing all this yet.

209
00:11:41,910 --> 00:11:42,840
You should rest.

210
00:11:43,390 --> 00:11:45,050
I'll take care of it tomorrow.

211
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:46,400
Alright then.

212
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:47,630
Mom,

213
00:11:48,150 --> 00:11:50,160
you must be exhausted
from moving these past couple of days.

214
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:52,420
Yan Ling wants me
to take good care of you.

215
00:11:52,550 --> 00:11:52,960
Mom,

216
00:11:54,150 --> 00:11:54,510
here,

217
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,170
sit down please.

218
00:11:57,070 --> 00:11:58,060
Try this—

219
00:11:58,390 --> 00:11:59,850
it's really comfortable.

220
00:12:01,670 --> 00:12:02,500
Thank you.

221
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:03,900
Is the pressure okay?

222
00:12:04,870 --> 00:12:05,670
It's perfect.

223
00:12:05,810 --> 00:12:06,300
Good.

224
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:08,420
Is Yan Ling asleep?

225
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:09,140
Yes, she is.

226
00:12:09,620 --> 00:12:12,020
She went to bed early
so she'll look her best

227
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:13,940
for the wedding photos tomorrow.

228
00:12:23,630 --> 00:12:25,160
Earlier, while tidying up,

229
00:12:25,310 --> 00:12:26,980
I came across your diploma.

230
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:28,720
Yeah,

231
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:31,970
I entered Tianfu Medical University
in 2004.

232
00:12:32,030 --> 00:12:34,290
Getting into such a prestigious school—

233
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:36,120
you must have been a top student.

234
00:12:36,550 --> 00:12:37,610
Yan Ling mentioned

235
00:12:38,020 --> 00:12:39,050
your father

236
00:12:39,510 --> 00:12:40,320
was once

237
00:12:40,840 --> 00:12:42,960
sent to work in Diannan
as an educated youth.

238
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:45,560
And your mother seemed
so cultured the other day—

239
00:12:45,560 --> 00:12:47,220
was she an educated youth too?

240
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:47,960
No,

241
00:12:49,030 --> 00:12:51,490
she worked as a health worker
in the commune.

242
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:54,600
I saw your mother
at the supermarket today.

243
00:12:58,320 --> 00:12:59,450
That's impossible.

244
00:13:00,390 --> 00:13:01,670
You must have mistaken her
for someone else.

245
00:13:01,670 --> 00:13:03,530
She looked just like your mother—

246
00:13:03,550 --> 00:13:05,080
even her voice was the same.

247
00:13:05,870 --> 00:13:07,670
I gave her my contact number too.

248
00:13:08,510 --> 00:13:10,320
It must have been a case
of mistaken identity.

249
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:12,320
She's in the Philippines right now—

250
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:14,510
unless she can be in two places at once.

251
00:13:14,510 --> 00:13:16,370
I've been teaching my whole life,

252
00:13:17,550 --> 00:13:20,080
and I've never once
misidentified a student.

253
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:26,100
Yan Ling has told you
everything about herself—

254
00:13:26,350 --> 00:13:28,150
she's given you her whole heart.

255
00:13:29,960 --> 00:13:30,600
I know.

256
00:13:31,480 --> 00:13:32,740
And I feel the same way.

257
00:13:34,660 --> 00:13:36,160
The most important thing

258
00:13:36,510 --> 00:13:38,570
between husband and wife is honesty.

259
00:13:38,950 --> 00:13:40,550
Yan Ling went through so much

260
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:42,040
before she found you.

261
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:44,270
I hope the two of you

262
00:13:44,270 --> 00:13:46,470
will cherish each other for a lifetime.

263
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:51,290
She's suffered so much in the past,

264
00:13:54,630 --> 00:13:56,080
and I hate myself

265
00:13:56,080 --> 00:13:58,480
for not being able
to protect her back then.

266
00:14:00,320 --> 00:14:01,480
I swear.

267
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:03,790
If anyone

268
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:06,140
ever bullies or hurts her from now on,

269
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:08,250
I will not let them get away with it.

270
00:14:14,510 --> 00:14:15,000
Mom,

271
00:14:16,760 --> 00:14:18,360
I've also made up my mind

272
00:14:18,760 --> 00:14:21,020
to spend the rest of my life
with Yan Ling.

273
00:14:25,280 --> 00:14:26,880
You should get some rest now—

274
00:14:27,240 --> 00:14:28,900
they say a typhoon is coming tomorrow

275
00:14:28,900 --> 00:14:29,950
with heavy rain.

276
00:14:32,750 --> 00:14:33,480
I'm going to check

277
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:35,630
that all the windows
and doors are closed.

278
00:14:35,630 --> 00:14:36,690
Get to sleep early.

279
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:45,840
Mom.

280
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:47,900
Goodnight.

281
00:15:18,980 --> 00:15:20,720
[Name: Dai Si Sheng]
[Chengyu Education Bureau]

282
00:15:27,850 --> 00:15:30,400
[Name: Dai Si Sheng]
[Chengyu Education Bureau]

283
00:15:35,250 --> 00:15:35,870
Hello,

284
00:15:36,120 --> 00:15:37,050
is this Si Sheng?

285
00:15:37,360 --> 00:15:38,000
It's me,

286
00:15:38,120 --> 00:15:38,750
Ms. Su.

287
00:15:40,960 --> 00:15:41,360
Hello?

288
00:15:42,630 --> 00:15:43,360
Yes, it's me.

289
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:45,480
I wanted to ask—

290
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:46,790
are you still

291
00:15:47,480 --> 00:15:50,320
working at the Chengyu Education Bureau?

292
00:15:50,820 --> 00:15:51,830
That's great.

293
00:15:53,030 --> 00:15:54,890
Could you help me look up a student

294
00:15:55,150 --> 00:15:56,480
from your Tianfu Medical University,

295
00:15:56,480 --> 00:15:58,140
named Luo Liang?

296
00:15:59,320 --> 00:16:00,980
She's already figured it out.

297
00:16:01,880 --> 00:16:02,640
I think

298
00:16:03,750 --> 00:16:05,410
you should arrange to meet her

299
00:16:05,480 --> 00:16:06,940
and be completely honest.

300
00:16:07,910 --> 00:16:09,870
Please send her a text later

301
00:16:10,830 --> 00:16:12,630
and ask to meet tomorrow at 10 AM,

302
00:16:12,910 --> 00:16:14,370
at that same supermarket.

303
00:16:16,250 --> 00:16:17,580
I appreciate your help.

304
00:16:17,740 --> 00:16:20,260
Let me know as soon as you find anything.

305
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:22,280
Okay.

306
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:23,940
Thanks for your hard work.

307
00:17:50,440 --> 00:17:50,960
Mom,

308
00:17:51,440 --> 00:17:51,960
don't trouble yourself.

309
00:17:51,960 --> 00:17:53,030
We don't have time to eat—

310
00:17:53,030 --> 00:17:54,370
we need to head out now.

311
00:17:54,510 --> 00:17:55,720
With the rain today, traffic might be bad.

312
00:17:55,720 --> 00:17:56,550
But I've already made breakfast.

313
00:17:56,550 --> 00:17:57,270
That's right.

314
00:17:57,270 --> 00:17:58,680
On a rainy day like this,
there's no need to go out for groceries.

315
00:17:58,680 --> 00:18:00,020
If you need anything,
just call us—

316
00:18:00,020 --> 00:18:01,750
we can pick it up on our way back.

317
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:02,830
Right, Mom.

318
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:04,180
Don't go outside.

319
00:18:04,310 --> 00:18:05,640
Just wait for us at home.

320
00:18:05,750 --> 00:18:08,160
But with such heavy rain,
can you still take photos?

321
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:10,310
Yes, today's shoot is indoors.

322
00:18:12,830 --> 00:18:14,490
I'll take two marinated eggs.

323
00:18:14,640 --> 00:18:15,700
Wait for us at home.

324
00:18:20,030 --> 00:18:20,800
Hurry up!

325
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:21,550
It tastes so good.

326
00:18:21,550 --> 00:18:22,580
We're going to be late.

327
00:18:22,580 --> 00:18:24,000
Mom's marinated eggs are amazing.

328
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:24,660
Take a bite.

329
00:18:24,960 --> 00:18:26,480
Mom, wait for us at home, okay?

330
00:18:26,480 --> 00:18:27,350
Mom, we're heading out now.

331
00:18:27,350 --> 00:18:27,880
Hurry up!

332
00:18:40,670 --> 00:18:42,350
[Ms. Su, tomorrow at 10 AM,]

333
00:18:42,370 --> 00:18:44,020
[same supermarket, let's have a chat.]

334
00:19:47,340 --> 00:19:49,340
[Construction Ahead, No Entry]

335
00:21:09,870 --> 00:21:12,030
Every time there's a typhoon
or heavy rain here,

336
00:21:12,030 --> 00:21:14,480
we open the manhole covers
on the road for drainage.

337
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:16,400
We always put up warning signs
to block off the road.

338
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:18,110
It's been like this for many years,

339
00:21:18,110 --> 00:21:20,440
and the nearby residents all know
to take a detour.

340
00:21:20,440 --> 00:21:21,920
We're not sure if it was a prank

341
00:21:21,920 --> 00:21:23,070
or a work error,

342
00:21:23,480 --> 00:21:25,480
but the warning sign was misplaced—

343
00:21:25,860 --> 00:21:27,510
and our neighborhood office
failed to notice.

344
00:21:27,510 --> 00:21:28,370
We will conduct

345
00:21:28,480 --> 00:21:30,540
a thorough review of our procedures.

346
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:55,140
Ms. Yan.

347
00:21:56,560 --> 00:21:57,310
Ms. Yan.

348
00:22:00,870 --> 00:22:01,800
Let me take that.

349
00:22:02,150 --> 00:22:03,750
These were her mother's belongings.

350
00:22:03,750 --> 00:22:04,400
According to the investigation,

351
00:22:04,400 --> 00:22:05,090
there is no surveillance
on the section of the road

352
00:22:05,090 --> 00:22:06,310
where the incident occurred.

353
00:22:06,310 --> 00:22:08,240
However, surveillance footage
from other sections

354
00:22:08,240 --> 00:22:09,200
shows

355
00:22:09,520 --> 00:22:10,240
that her mother

356
00:22:10,240 --> 00:22:11,970
was walking alone on that road.

357
00:22:12,440 --> 00:22:15,880
It's highly likely that her death
was an accidental drowning.

358
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:16,750
Please accept our condolences.

359
00:22:16,750 --> 00:22:17,350
Thank you.

360
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:44,340
Uncle, Auntie.

361
00:23:45,020 --> 00:23:45,810
You're back.

362
00:23:46,110 --> 00:23:47,240
Please, have a seat.

363
00:23:48,880 --> 00:23:49,750
She hasn't woken up, has she?

364
00:23:49,750 --> 00:23:50,550
No, not yet.

365
00:23:53,090 --> 00:23:54,550
She hadn't slept for days—

366
00:23:54,790 --> 00:23:56,880
she finally took a sleeping pill
to get some sleep.

367
00:23:56,880 --> 00:23:58,200
How's Jiale?

368
00:23:58,400 --> 00:23:59,350
Lu is with him.

369
00:23:59,790 --> 00:24:01,120
Jiale is so thoughtful.

370
00:24:01,200 --> 00:24:03,590
He said he wanted to stay
with Lu for a few days.

371
00:24:03,590 --> 00:24:05,070
He's worried that if he stayed with us,

372
00:24:05,070 --> 00:24:06,610
his mom will still have
to take care of him.

373
00:24:06,610 --> 00:24:08,540
What a wonderful family you are...

374
00:24:09,510 --> 00:24:11,910
Why did something like this
have to happen?

375
00:24:13,750 --> 00:24:14,590
Luo,

376
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:18,120
if there's anything you need,
just say it.

377
00:24:18,120 --> 00:24:18,920
We see Yan Ling

378
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:20,700
as our own daughter.

379
00:24:22,160 --> 00:24:23,160
Uncle, Auntie,

380
00:24:23,550 --> 00:24:25,410
your being here to watch over her—

381
00:24:25,550 --> 00:24:26,680
so I could go settle Jiale

382
00:24:26,680 --> 00:24:27,600
and get the phone repaired—

383
00:24:27,600 --> 00:24:29,200
has already been a huge help.

384
00:24:31,880 --> 00:24:34,010
I really shouldn't have left her side.

385
00:24:34,750 --> 00:24:35,950
I really wanted to fix

386
00:24:36,760 --> 00:24:38,290
her mother's phone for her—

387
00:24:39,110 --> 00:24:41,510
it would mean a lot,
something to hold on to.

388
00:24:41,550 --> 00:24:43,410
You're very considerate.

389
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:45,160
With you by her side,

390
00:24:45,750 --> 00:24:46,750
Yan Ling's mother

391
00:24:47,160 --> 00:24:48,350
can rest easy.

392
00:24:49,200 --> 00:24:50,550
Now that you're back,

393
00:24:52,160 --> 00:24:53,290
we should head home.

394
00:24:53,680 --> 00:24:54,740
We'll be going now.

395
00:24:55,020 --> 00:24:55,960
Let me see you out.

396
00:24:55,960 --> 00:24:56,440
No need,

397
00:24:56,870 --> 00:24:57,970
stay with Yan Ling.

398
00:24:58,440 --> 00:24:59,700
It's the least I can do.

399
00:25:13,070 --> 00:25:13,510
Mom.

400
00:25:14,510 --> 00:25:14,830
Mom.

401
00:25:15,640 --> 00:25:17,290
-Ling, help me!
-Mom.

402
00:25:51,310 --> 00:25:55,080
[Respectfully offered
by student Du Hong in mourning.]

403
00:25:57,200 --> 00:25:59,400
Please accept my deepest condolences.

404
00:25:59,550 --> 00:26:00,110
Uncle.

405
00:26:01,780 --> 00:26:03,450
Please accept my deepest condolences.

406
00:26:03,450 --> 00:26:05,650
Please accept my deepest condolences.

407
00:26:12,080 --> 00:26:14,280
Please accept my deepest condolences.

408
00:26:14,550 --> 00:26:16,510
Please accept my deepest condolences.

409
00:26:16,510 --> 00:26:18,710
Please accept my deepest condolences.

410
00:26:19,250 --> 00:26:20,910
[A loving mother]

411
00:26:19,310 --> 00:26:21,510
Please accept my deepest condolences.

412
00:26:21,590 --> 00:26:23,310
Please accept my deepest condolences.

413
00:26:23,310 --> 00:26:25,510
Please accept my deepest condolences.

414
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:28,080
Please accept my deepest condolences.

415
00:26:33,200 --> 00:26:35,040
[Tomb of Loving Father Yan Qianhe
and Loving Mother Su Ruiqin]

416
00:27:06,150 --> 00:27:07,630
[Doctor of Lihai University]

417
00:27:07,650 --> 00:27:09,290
[Honored with the title
of Outstanding Young Academic Worker]

418
00:27:25,090 --> 00:27:25,920
[In Memoriam]

419
00:27:25,970 --> 00:27:26,780
[Doctor of Lihai University]

420
00:27:26,810 --> 00:27:28,020
[Honored with the title
of Outstanding Young Academic Worker]

421
00:27:29,240 --> 00:27:31,550
[Campus Hall of Fame]

422
00:28:04,250 --> 00:28:06,200
[Tomb of Loving Father Yan Qianhe
and Loving Mother Su Ruiqin]

423
00:28:41,270 --> 00:28:43,640
Am I dreaming?

424
00:28:51,770 --> 00:28:52,970
You're not dreaming.

425
00:28:54,550 --> 00:28:56,010
Mom has gone to be with Dad.

426
00:28:59,240 --> 00:29:01,090
Why?

427
00:29:05,640 --> 00:29:07,110
Why?

428
00:29:08,920 --> 00:29:10,910
But she had already forgiven me.

429
00:29:15,350 --> 00:29:17,550
She told me I must live on fully.

430
00:29:20,880 --> 00:29:22,240
I listened to her.

431
00:29:23,790 --> 00:29:24,440
I know.

432
00:29:24,800 --> 00:29:26,870
Mom had forgiven me.

433
00:29:27,510 --> 00:29:28,250
I know.

434
00:29:30,510 --> 00:29:31,250
I know.

435
00:29:32,590 --> 00:29:33,650
Don't be like this.

436
00:29:33,890 --> 00:29:36,170
It was an accident. It was an accident.

437
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:37,440
It was an accident.

438
00:29:37,440 --> 00:29:39,090
Why did she have to leave?

439
00:29:39,160 --> 00:29:41,000
I don't want this...

440
00:29:41,790 --> 00:29:42,850
Don't be like this.

441
00:29:43,240 --> 00:29:44,680
She would never have wanted to leave you.

442
00:29:44,680 --> 00:29:45,740
Don't be like this.

443
00:29:46,070 --> 00:29:47,270
It wasn't her choice.

444
00:29:47,940 --> 00:29:49,160
It wasn't her choice.

445
00:29:49,760 --> 00:29:50,760
You still have us.

446
00:29:51,400 --> 00:29:52,600
You still have Jiale.

447
00:29:54,400 --> 00:29:55,460
We won't leave you,

448
00:29:55,550 --> 00:29:56,140
okay?

449
00:29:56,240 --> 00:29:57,300
We won't leave you.

450
00:30:03,400 --> 00:30:04,130
I'm here.

451
00:30:22,030 --> 00:30:23,110
I'm right here.

452
00:30:52,640 --> 00:30:53,750
Wait for us at home.

453
00:31:42,740 --> 00:31:46,580
[Lihai City; Unknown Incoming Call]

454
00:31:52,030 --> 00:31:52,590
Hello?

455
00:31:52,680 --> 00:31:53,270
Ms. Su?

456
00:31:55,590 --> 00:31:57,160
No, this isn't Ms. Su.

457
00:31:58,510 --> 00:32:00,270
This is Yan Ling, Ms. Su's daughter.

458
00:32:00,270 --> 00:32:01,240
May I ask who's calling?

459
00:32:01,240 --> 00:32:02,570
I used to be her student.

460
00:32:02,830 --> 00:32:04,830
Last week, Ms. Su called and asked me

461
00:32:04,830 --> 00:32:05,640
to check on a student

462
00:32:05,640 --> 00:32:07,960
from the Class of 2004
at Tianfu Medical University,

463
00:32:07,960 --> 00:32:08,900
named Luo Liang.

464
00:32:09,110 --> 00:32:09,960
I looked it up,

465
00:32:10,570 --> 00:32:12,570
and indeed, there is such a student.

466
00:32:12,790 --> 00:32:15,740
He came from Jingxiong, Diannan,
and was enrolled in 2004.

467
00:32:15,740 --> 00:32:17,140
He was quite remarkable—

468
00:32:17,750 --> 00:32:19,480
both his parents had passed away,

469
00:32:19,480 --> 00:32:20,680
and he was raised by the village,

470
00:32:20,680 --> 00:32:23,940
yet he still managed to achieve
such outstanding results.

471
00:32:24,480 --> 00:32:25,410
What did you say?

472
00:32:28,110 --> 00:32:29,780
Both parents passed away?

473
00:32:31,600 --> 00:32:33,350
Ms. Su specifically asked me

474
00:32:33,590 --> 00:32:35,590
to look into his family background.

475
00:32:36,030 --> 00:32:37,920
His college entrance exam file states

476
00:32:37,920 --> 00:32:39,120
that he was an orphan.

477
00:32:51,750 --> 00:32:52,680
I'm home,

478
00:32:59,200 --> 00:32:59,960
Honey.

479
00:33:07,400 --> 00:33:08,110
Honey?

480
00:33:25,680 --> 00:33:27,710
Let's sort through these another day,

481
00:33:27,710 --> 00:33:28,230
no rush.

482
00:33:36,480 --> 00:33:37,080
Come here.

483
00:33:48,850 --> 00:33:51,430
I've never seen any photos
of you as a child.

484
00:33:54,520 --> 00:33:57,180
There are a few back at my hometown,
but not many.

485
00:33:57,750 --> 00:33:59,190
I moved around a lot for school and work,

486
00:33:59,190 --> 00:34:00,050
and I lost them.

487
00:34:03,740 --> 00:34:05,740
There's something I need to ask you.

488
00:34:07,430 --> 00:34:08,090
What is it?

489
00:34:10,070 --> 00:34:10,800
That person

490
00:34:12,690 --> 00:34:14,550
we met at the restaurant that day—

491
00:34:16,340 --> 00:34:18,139
was she your biological mother?

492
00:34:22,179 --> 00:34:23,199
What do you mean?

493
00:34:34,280 --> 00:34:35,580
I got a call

494
00:34:36,280 --> 00:34:38,340
from one of my mom's former students.

495
00:34:40,469 --> 00:34:42,010
He said my mom had asked him

496
00:34:42,610 --> 00:34:45,139
to check your
college entrance exam records—

497
00:34:45,929 --> 00:34:47,139
and it stated

498
00:34:47,850 --> 00:34:50,050
that both your parents had passed away,

499
00:34:50,290 --> 00:34:51,620
that you were an orphan.

500
00:34:59,340 --> 00:35:00,540
You investigated me?

501
00:35:01,550 --> 00:35:02,400
Not me,

502
00:35:02,670 --> 00:35:03,590
it was Mom.

503
00:35:04,660 --> 00:35:06,060
But that's not the point.

504
00:35:07,200 --> 00:35:09,290
I want to know what's really going on.

505
00:35:10,890 --> 00:35:11,650
The father

506
00:35:12,010 --> 00:35:13,540
who just passed away in May,

507
00:35:14,180 --> 00:35:16,020
and the mother I just met—

508
00:35:16,590 --> 00:35:17,630
who are they?

509
00:35:19,590 --> 00:35:21,390
Are they your adoptive parents?

510
00:35:22,930 --> 00:35:24,420
Why did you lie to me?

511
00:35:25,670 --> 00:35:28,270
I really didn't expect you guys
to be like this.

512
00:35:28,800 --> 00:35:29,480
You don't even

513
00:35:29,480 --> 00:35:31,610
care about the basic trust between us.

514
00:35:33,030 --> 00:35:34,690
What else is there left to say?

515
00:35:36,070 --> 00:35:37,030
Trust?

516
00:35:38,840 --> 00:35:41,120
Isn't trust built on mutual honesty?

517
00:35:41,280 --> 00:35:43,250
Just tell me the truth.

518
00:35:45,630 --> 00:35:46,960
I know you're grieving

519
00:35:46,960 --> 00:35:48,280
your mom's sudden passing,

520
00:35:48,280 --> 00:35:49,200
and so am I.

521
00:35:49,360 --> 00:35:50,070
I don't want to say anything

522
00:35:50,070 --> 00:35:51,960
that would hurt you or her.

523
00:35:52,740 --> 00:35:53,800
But what you did—

524
00:35:53,800 --> 00:35:55,400
investigating behind my back—

525
00:35:55,400 --> 00:35:56,730
it feels shameful to me.

526
00:35:57,880 --> 00:35:58,810
I'm hurt.

527
00:35:59,120 --> 00:35:59,920
Don't walk away.

528
00:35:59,920 --> 00:36:00,650
Talk to me.

529
00:36:00,920 --> 00:36:01,880
What happened?

530
00:36:01,880 --> 00:36:02,630
I want to know.

531
00:36:02,630 --> 00:36:03,400
Tell me.

532
00:36:03,400 --> 00:36:03,920
Tell me!

533
00:36:03,920 --> 00:36:04,920
-Let me pass.
-Don't go.

534
00:36:04,920 --> 00:36:06,250
Just give me some space.

535
00:36:06,920 --> 00:36:07,520
Luo Liang.

536
00:36:07,960 --> 00:36:08,560
Luo Liang!

537
00:36:09,660 --> 00:36:10,410
Luo Liang!

538
00:36:14,670 --> 00:36:15,270
Luo Liang,

539
00:36:16,480 --> 00:36:17,280
open the door.

540
00:36:18,140 --> 00:36:20,470
Come out and talk to me, please,
Luo Liang.

541
00:36:24,070 --> 00:36:26,730
Whatever you're going through,
you can tell me.

542
00:36:28,190 --> 00:36:29,000
I believe you must

543
00:36:29,000 --> 00:36:31,060
have had your reasons for doing this.

544
00:36:32,750 --> 00:36:35,880
But avoiding me like this—
what kind of attitude is that?

545
00:36:37,480 --> 00:36:38,210
Luo Liang,

546
00:36:38,860 --> 00:36:40,720
if you refuse to tell me anything,

547
00:36:41,630 --> 00:36:44,160
how are we supposed
to move forward together?

548
00:37:56,150 --> 00:37:56,810
Keep going!

549
00:37:57,120 --> 00:37:58,580
Feng, where are you going?

550
00:37:59,030 --> 00:37:59,960
What a buzzkill!

551
00:38:00,490 --> 00:38:02,090
Whatever. Let's keep going.

552
00:38:04,030 --> 00:38:05,020
I've actually been

553
00:38:05,020 --> 00:38:07,480
planning to look for you
these past few days.

554
00:38:08,570 --> 00:38:09,970
I killed someone for you,

555
00:38:10,590 --> 00:38:11,290
didn't I?

556
00:38:20,650 --> 00:38:22,110
If you want me to trust you,

557
00:38:23,070 --> 00:38:25,000
show me what you're capable of.

558
00:38:26,650 --> 00:38:27,970
Consider this a test.

559
00:38:42,830 --> 00:38:43,950
Just moving a sign?

560
00:38:44,310 --> 00:38:45,240
That's all?

561
00:38:46,460 --> 00:38:47,610
That's all.

562
00:39:01,370 --> 00:39:06,340
[Construction Ahead, No Entry]

563
00:39:13,990 --> 00:39:15,370
[Construction Ahead, No Entry]

564
00:39:50,110 --> 00:39:50,840
To be honest,

565
00:39:50,840 --> 00:39:52,440
I was really scared at first.

566
00:39:52,800 --> 00:39:54,450
I stayed out of town for many days

567
00:39:54,450 --> 00:39:56,110
and didn't dare to contact you.

568
00:39:56,110 --> 00:39:57,170
Then I saw the news—

569
00:39:57,920 --> 00:40:00,330
it actually got written off
as an accident.

570
00:40:00,710 --> 00:40:01,940
Just a warning sign,

571
00:40:02,320 --> 00:40:04,790
and you took
out your mother-in-law that easily.

572
00:40:04,790 --> 00:40:06,300
But how did you make sure

573
00:40:06,710 --> 00:40:07,880
she showed up exactly

574
00:40:07,880 --> 00:40:09,190
where you wanted?

575
00:40:11,280 --> 00:40:12,070
Impressive.

576
00:40:25,070 --> 00:40:26,110
I know who she is.

577
00:40:28,760 --> 00:40:30,420
When I was searching the news,

578
00:40:30,590 --> 00:40:31,920
I saw you

579
00:40:32,560 --> 00:40:34,070
and Ms. Yan in the scene photos

580
00:40:34,070 --> 00:40:36,480
and found
out the deceased's surname was Su.

581
00:40:36,480 --> 00:40:37,710
Previously, that incident between Ms. Yan

582
00:40:37,710 --> 00:40:39,130
and the CEO of Oceanvision International

583
00:40:39,130 --> 00:40:40,650
blew up online—

584
00:40:40,920 --> 00:40:42,910
her personal info was everywhere.

585
00:40:44,480 --> 00:40:46,670
Her mother's surname was also Su,

586
00:40:47,710 --> 00:40:49,640
to be specific, the full name was Su

587
00:40:49,670 --> 00:40:50,070
Rui

588
00:40:51,110 --> 00:40:51,590
qin.

589
00:40:54,510 --> 00:40:55,910
You figured all that out—

590
00:40:56,030 --> 00:40:57,560
feeling proud of yourself?

591
00:40:59,430 --> 00:41:01,630
Aren't you afraid I'll go to the police?

592
00:41:05,480 --> 00:41:06,400
Why would I be?

593
00:41:07,880 --> 00:41:09,740
You're the one who moved the sign.

594
00:41:09,920 --> 00:41:11,580
What does it have to do with me?

595
00:41:17,320 --> 00:41:18,580
Just kidding, Mister.

596
00:41:19,120 --> 00:41:19,920
Don't worry,

597
00:41:20,590 --> 00:41:22,480
this is my proof of loyalty to you.

598
00:41:23,840 --> 00:41:25,170
But I'm really curious—

599
00:41:25,430 --> 00:41:26,940
why did you want her dead?

600
00:41:27,590 --> 00:41:28,570
Taking a life

601
00:41:29,100 --> 00:41:30,320
just to control Ms. Yan—

602
00:41:30,320 --> 00:41:32,180
is it really worth going that far?

603
00:41:37,050 --> 00:41:38,010
Human life

604
00:41:38,900 --> 00:41:40,430
in essence, is no different

605
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:42,440
from the flowers, plants,

606
00:41:42,440 --> 00:41:44,000
or earthworms in the soil.

607
00:41:45,310 --> 00:41:46,440
When the time comes,

608
00:41:46,710 --> 00:41:47,640
death will come.

609
00:41:48,320 --> 00:41:51,520
Whether it's this accident
or that one, it's inevitable.

610
00:41:52,670 --> 00:41:54,000
The only difference is,

611
00:41:55,840 --> 00:41:57,510
who pulls the trigger—

612
00:41:59,110 --> 00:42:00,000
fate or us,

613
00:42:01,840 --> 00:42:03,190
ordinary people.

614
00:42:06,710 --> 00:42:07,660
So,

615
00:42:07,960 --> 00:42:11,020
would you be willing to teach me
how to pull the trigger?

616
00:42:15,110 --> 00:42:16,640
Help me with one more thing.

617
00:42:18,440 --> 00:42:22,900
[The Dark Romance]

618
00:42:25,190 --> 00:42:27,320
It's fixed. Try not to get it wet again.

619
00:42:29,150 --> 00:42:30,070
I'll give you a discount.

620
00:42:30,070 --> 00:42:30,670
That'll be 260.

621
00:42:30,670 --> 00:42:31,670
You can scan here.

622
00:42:31,770 --> 00:42:33,250
[Ms. Su, tomorrow at 10 AM,]

623
00:42:33,280 --> 00:42:35,530
[same supermarket, let's have a chat.]

624
